ted data. For example, RATs are often trained on older data; but if a jurisdiction has since instituted pretrial reforms, the RAT will reflect outdated practices rather than current ones. If a new diversion program is introduced to decrease pretrial detention and recidivism, the RAT does not take this into account, hiding any potential effects the reform has and reinforcing historical trends.'),(3104,252,'_more_info_for_pop-up_2','field_62b570b77557d'),(3105,252,'title_for_pop-up_3',''),(3106,252,'_title_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5702b1175d'),(3107,252,'description_for_pop-up_3',''),(3108,252,'_description_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5706511762'),(3109,252,'subtitle_3',''),(3110,252,'_subtitle_3','field_62b57eb6e3372'),(3111,252,'more_info_for_pop-up_3',''),(3112,252,'_more_info_for_pop-up_3','field_62b570c37557e'),(3113,252,'lilst_items_item_1','“Public Safety Risk Assessment Clearinghouse,” Bureau of Justice Assistance, US Department of Justice, https://psrac.bja.ojp.gov/ '),(3114,252,'_lilst_items_item_1','field_62b570ea75580'),(3115,252,'lilst_items_item_2','“Use of Valid Actuarial Assessments of Risks and Needs,” National Parole Resource Center, https://nationalparoleresourcecenter.org/action-guide-use-of-valid-actuarial-assessments-of-risks-and-needs/selecting-and-validating-an-assessment-instrument.htm '),(3116,252,'_lilst_items_item_2','field_62b570f575581'),(3117,252,'lilst_items_item_3','Alex Chohlas-Wood, “Understanding risk assessment instruments in criminal justice,” https://www.brookings.edu/research/understanding-risk-assessment-instruments-in-criminal-justice/'),(3118,252,'_lilst_items_item_3','field_62b570f675582'),(3119,252,'lilst_items_item_4',''),(3120,252,'_lilst_items_item_4','field_62b570f775583'),(3121,252,'lilst_items_item_5',''),(3122,252,'_lilst_items_item_5','field_62b5a234d64c3'),(3123,252,'lilst_items',''),(3124,252,'_lilst_items','field_62b570c97557f'),(3125,252,'lilst_items_2_item_1',''),(3126,252,'_lilst_items_2_item_1','field_62b5a238d64c