ement'),(3275,257,'_subtitle_1','field_62b570927557b'),(3276,257,'more_info_for_pop-up_1','During parole, RATs are used for case management, much the same as they are in jails and prisons. Parole authorities are responsible for ensuring previously incarcerated individuals are not rearrested or break conditions of their parole. They employ RATs to evaluate risk factors for recidivism, and to provide services to minimize this risk. RATs also measure and track “progress” of individuals over the course of their time in probation, and in the criminal legal system overall. Like case management at other decision points, during parole RATs are specialized to evaluate risks related to violence, sexual offenses, health issues, addiction, mental illness, behavior, attitudes, and other areas.'),(3277,257,'_more_info_for_pop-up_1','field_62b5709e7557c'),(3278,257,'title_for_pop-up_2',''),(3279,257,'_title_for_pop-up_2','field_62b570281175c'),(3280,257,'description_for_pop-up_2',''),(3281,257,'_description_for_pop-up_2','field_62b5706211761'),(3282,257,'subtitle_2',''),(3283,257,'_subtitle_2','field_62b57eb4e3371'),(3284,257,'more_info_for_pop-up_2',''),(3285,257,'_more_info_for_pop-up_2','field_62b570b77557d'),(3286,257,'title_for_pop-up_3',''),(3287,257,'_title_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5702b1175d'),(3288,257,'description_for_pop-up_3',''),(3289,257,'_description_for_pop-up_3','field_62b5706511762'),(3290,257,'subtitle_3',''),(3291,257,'_subtitle_3','field_62b57eb6e3372'),(3292,257,'more_info_for_pop-up_3',''),(3293,257,'_more_info_for_pop-up_3','field_62b570c37557e'),(3294,257,'lilst_items_item_1',''),(3295,257,'_lilst_items_item_1','field_62b570ea75580'),(3296,257,'lilst_items_item_2',''),(3297,257,'_lilst_items_item_2','field_62b570f575581'),(3298,257,'lilst_items_item_3',''),(3299,257,'_lilst_items_item_3','field_62b570f675582'),(3300,257,'lilst_items_item_4',''),(3301,257,'_lilst_items_item_4','field_62b570f775583'),(3302,257,'lilst_items_item_5',''),(3303,257,'_lilst_items_